title WordPress REST Base Controller Lifecycle\n<size:11><i>WP_REST_Controller — Abstract template: permission gates, CRUD stubs, DB/response preparation, context filtering (since WP 4.7.0)</i></size>

|#E8F4FD|REST Server|
start
:Receive HTTP Request\n(namespace / rest_base / id?);

note right
  WP REST server resolves
  route registered via
  **register_routes()** stub.
  Subclass must call
  register_rest_route() here
  or _doing_it_wrong() fires.
end note

:Resolve permission check method\nbased on HTTP verb;

|#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
:Execute permission check\nget_{items|item|create|update|delete}_items_permissions_check($request);

note right
  Base stubs return
  **WP_Error('invalid-method', 405)**.
  Subclass overrides must call
  current_user_can() or
  custom auth logic.
end note

|#E8F4FD|REST Server|
if (Permission check returns WP_Error?) then (yes — 403 / 401)
  :Build error response\nfrom WP_Error status & message;
  :Return HTTP error response\n(no action method called);
  stop
else (no — returns true)
endif

:Dispatch to action method\nbased on HTTP verb;

if (HTTP Method?) then (GET /namespace/base — collection)

  |#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
  :get_items($request)\nQuery database for items\napplying pagination, search, filters;

  note right
    **get_collection_params()** provides:
    context, page (default=1),
    per_page (default=10, max=100),
    search query parameter.
  end note

  :Iterate over result set;

  repeat
    :prepare_item_for_response($item, $request)\nMap DB/model object to REST shape;

    |#EAF4EA|WP_REST_Controller\n(Abstract Base)|
    :add_additional_fields_to_object($prepared, $request)\nRead $wp_rest_additional_fields global;\nInvoke get_callback per registered field;

    :filter_response_by_context($data, $context);

    note right
      **CONCRETE method.**
      Calls get_item_schema() (cached in $schema since WP 5.3.0),
      then rest_filter_response_by_context().
      Fields included only if schema 'context' array
      contains request context: **view / edit / embed**.
    end note

    :prepare_response_for_collection($response)\nUnwrap WP_REST_Response:\n$response->get_data()\n+ WP_REST_Server::get_compact_response_links();

    note right
      Injects **_links** key if present.
      If $response is not a WP_REST_Response
      instance → returned as-is.
    end note

  repeat while (More items?) is (yes)
  -> no;

  |#E8F4FD|REST Server|
  :Return WP_REST_Response\n(collection array with _links);
  stop

elseif (HTTP Method?) then (GET /namespace/base/{id} — single item)

  |#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
  :get_item($request)\nFetch single item from database;

  :prepare_item_for_response($item, $request)\nMap DB object to REST shape;

  |#EAF4EA|WP_REST_Controller\n(Abstract Base)|
  :add_additional_fields_to_object($prepared, $request)\nAppend registered additional fields;

  :get_fields_for_response($request)\nFilter schema properties by context\n+ optional _fields param;\nalways includes _links / _embedded;

  :filter_response_by_context($data, $context)\nStrip fields not valid for current context;

  |#E8F4FD|REST Server|
  :Return WP_REST_Response\n(single item);
  stop

elseif (HTTP Method?) then (POST / PUT / PATCH — create or update)

  |#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
  :create_item($request)\nor update_item($request);

  :prepare_item_for_database($request)\nMap WP_REST_Request fields\nto DB object structure;

  note right
    **Protected stub** — subclass must override.
    Returns stdObject for DB insert/update
    or **WP_Error** to abort.
  end note

  if (prepare_item_for_database returns WP_Error?) then (yes)
    |#E8F4FD|REST Server|
    :Return error response\n(abort create/update);
    stop
  else (no — returns DB object)
  endif

  :Execute DB insert / update\n(wp_insert_post, $wpdb->insert, etc.);

  |#EAF4EA|WP_REST_Controller\n(Abstract Base)|
  :update_additional_fields_for_object($object, $request)\nInvoke update_callback per registered additional field;

  |#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
  :prepare_item_for_response($saved_item, $request)\nMap saved DB item to REST shape;

  |#EAF4EA|WP_REST_Controller\n(Abstract Base)|
  :add_additional_fields_to_object($prepared, $request);

  :filter_response_by_context($data, $context);

  |#E8F4FD|REST Server|
  :Return WP_REST_Response\n(201 Created or 200 OK — single item);
  stop

else (DELETE /namespace/base/{id})

  |#FFF8E7|Concrete Subclass\n(e.g. WP_REST_Posts_Controller)|
  :delete_item($request)\nPrepare trashed / before-delete response\nfor return;

  :Execute DB delete / trash\n(wp_delete_post, $wpdb->delete, etc.);

  |#E8F4FD|REST Server|
  :Return WP_REST_Response\n(200 OK — deleted item data or empty);
  stop

endif

@enduml
